In a speech at the Heritage Foundation, Vice President Mike Pence discussed the economy, national defense, and the need for Congress to pass the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). He highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration in rebuilding the military, confronting Iran, and appointing conservative judges to the federal courts. Pence also praised the administration's economic policies, including tax cuts, deregulation, and increased American energy production. He called on Congress to pass the USMCA, stating that it would benefit American workers and strengthen the economy. Pence ended his speech by emphasizing the importance of the Constitution and the need to uphold its principles.